<item>
            <title>[SOLR-5943] SolrCmdDistributor does not distribute the openSearcher parameter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5943</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The openSearcher parameter in a commit command is totally ignored by the SolrCmdDistributor :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;SolrCmdDistributor.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; void addCommit(UpdateRequest ureq, CommitUpdateCommand cmd) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (cmd == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;;
    ureq.setAction(cmd.optimize ? AbstractUpdateRequest.ACTION.OPTIMIZE
        : AbstractUpdateRequest.ACTION.COMMIT, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;, cmd.waitSearcher, cmd.maxOptimizeSegments, cmd.softCommit, cmd.expungeDeletes);
  }&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the SolrJ API should take this parameter in account as well.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
